      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Reaction of acetone with D<sub>3</sub>O<sup>+</sup> yields hexadeuterioacetone. That is, all the hydrogens in acetone are exchanged for deuterium. Review the mechanism of mercuric-ion-catalyzed alkyne hydration, and then propose a mechanism for this deuterium incorporation.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdGtTIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--963276e5e9460c343e0ab9e8ea1a0e79d1e493e5/OChem_09_EC_022.jpg\" alt=\"The figure shows the reaction of acetone with tri-deuterium oxide to form hexadeuterioacetone.\">",
